    "b-00-vocab-overview-title-1": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-title-1",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Block vocabulary"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-lead-2": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-lead-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "These docs are written primarily for "
        },
        {
          "insert": "agents",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " to read. The markdown render ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "projectToMarkdown",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " in docs-model, driving the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs render",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " / "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs grep",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " CLI and the backend "
        },
        {
          "insert": "GET /api/markdown",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") is the agent surface: every block type defines a deterministic, greppable markdown form, so an agent never has to parse "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " just to read a document. The workbench renders the human view from the same blocks."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-fourteen-3": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-fourteen-3",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "kind": "Decision",
        "title": "Sixteen types and no more",
        "tone": "decision"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The author surface stays deliberately minimal. The source of truth is "
        },
        {
          "insert": "DOC_BLOCK_TYPES",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " in docs-model's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc-schema.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": exactly sixteen type strings. A small vocabulary keeps the render stable, the editor learnable, and the agent edit surface enumerable."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-doctrine-intro-4": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-doctrine-intro-4",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "For documenting agentic systems, three of those types carry the whole model:"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-doctrine-5": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-doctrine-5",
      "type": "quote",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A state-shape block carries the shape of state and an example instance side by side; an interaction-surface block lists the operations that change or query it; annotated code blocks hold the source evidence."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-flavour-history-6": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-flavour-history-6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Naming history, in one line: a block's kind field is "
        },
        {
          "insert": "type",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — the BlockSuite-heritage key "
        },
        {
          "insert": "flavour",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " went through a full wire-format rename and survives only as a READ alias that validation normalizes into "
        },
        {
          "insert": "type",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "; writes always emit canonical "
        },
        {
          "insert": "type",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-coercion-7": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-coercion-7",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "kind": "Decision",
        "title": "Retired types never break a corpus",
        "tone": "decision"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Validation never rejects a retired or unknown block type. After legacy "
        },
        {
          "insert": "flavour",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " aliasing, any block whose type is a string but not one of the 16 canonical types coerces to a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "callout",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/40-block-vocabulary/10-rich-text/14-callout"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", preserving the old type name as "
        },
        {
          "insert": "props.kind",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (unless the block already carries its own non-empty "
        },
        {
          "insert": "kind",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "); props, text, and children carry over verbatim. That is how the canvas sibling's semantic cards (requirement, decision, constraint, ...) load with zero file rewrites — coerced blocks simply canonicalize on their next save."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-h-8": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-h-8",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Three groups, nine components"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-model-9": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-model-9",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The model has no runtime category constant — the grouping lives in two places. First, "
        },
        {
          "insert": "DOC_BLOCK_TYPES",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " declares the sixteen types in three commented groups: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "core text & structure",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (paragraph, heading, list-item, quote, code, callout, divider), "
        },
        {
          "insert": "structured / engineering",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (structured-table, file-tree, interaction-surface, state-shape), and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "diagram & media",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (mermaid, canvas, sequence, image, video). Second, nine component bundles in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "components/<name>/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " own the sixteen types exactly once: rich-text owns the eight text-flow types (including image and video), while code, mermaid, file-tree, structured-table, interaction-surface, state-shape, canvas, and sequence each own their namesake."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-pages-10": {
      "id": "b-00-vocab-overview-groups-pages-10",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "These pages file the types on a third, reader-facing axis that follows the folder numbering: the 10s are the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "rich-text blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (the seven core text & structure types), the 20s are the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "object blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (typed-props state carriers: the structured / engineering four plus mermaid, sequence, and canvas), and the 30s are the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "media blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (image and video). Same sixteen types, sliced by how an agent edits them: rich-text blocks edit through delta text, object blocks through typed props and actions, media blocks through asset references."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-vocab-overview-index-h-11": {
